data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['lepəd]
*danh từ
 ■(động vật học) con báo
 ▸can the leopard change his spots?
 ■đánh chết cái nết không chừa

Anh - Anh
leopard
■ noun (fem. leopardess) a large solitary cat that has a fawn or brown coat with black spots, found in the forests of Africa and southern Asia. [Panthera pardus.]
⁃ Heraldry a lion passant guardant as in the arms of England.
⁃ [as modifier] spotted like a leopard.
Origin
ME: via OFr. from late L. leopardus, from late Gk leopardos, from leōn 'lion' + pardos (see pard).

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
leopard
n.
1) a snow leopard
2) a young leopard is a cub
3) a female leopard is a leopardess
